                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1007">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hill</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Bowen</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-04-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 25, 1902</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Hill states that the Government of the United States regards the course of
                    the Government of Venezuela respecting the steamer <hi rend="italic">Viking</hi>
                    as contrary to international law, and requests that the Venezuelan consul be
                    directed to issue clearance papers or that those of the United States consul be
                    respected, and that prompt action is required.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
